To compile

1. To create binary file from asm or nasm file execute script.
    $ ./compile64 nameOftheFile  (without extension)
    
2. Execute binary: $ ./nameOftheFile

Install repository

$sudo apt-get install nasm build-essential

- with -y flag to quickly install the packages and dependencies

- nasm
General-purpose x86 assembler
Netwide Assembler. NASM will currently output flat-form binary files, a.out, COFF and ELF Unix object files, 
and Microsoft 16-bit DOS and Win32 object files. General-purpose x86 assembler

- build-essential contain a bunch of new packages including gcc, g++ and make.

